net.bytebuddy

Interface ByteBuddy.Definable<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of the definable object.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ByteBuddy.Definable.Defined, ByteBuddy.Definable.Undefined
    Enclosing class:
    ByteBuddy

    protected static interface ByteBuddy.Definable<T>
    Any definable instance is either ByteBuddy.Definable.Defined when a value is provided or ByteBuddy.Definable.Undefined if a value is not provided. A defined definable will return its defined value on request while an undefined definable will return the provided default.

      A representation of an undefined ByteBuddy.Definable.
